In $ \triangle ABC$ points $ D$ and $ E$ lie on $ \overline{BC}$ and $ \overline{AC}$, respectively. If $ \overline{AD}$ and $ \overline{BE}$ intersect at $ T$ so that $ AT/DT = 3$ and $ BT/ET = 4$, what is $ CD/BD$?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(2cm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt));

pair A = (0,0);
pair C = (2,0);
pair B = dir(57.5)*2;
pair E = waypoint(C--A,0.25);
pair D = waypoint(C--B,0.25);
pair T = intersectionpoint(D--A,E--B);

label("$B$",B,NW);label("$A$",A,SW);label("$C$",C,SE);label("$D$",D,NE);label("$E$",E,S);label("$T$",T,2*W+N);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D);
draw(B--E);
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \frac {1}{8}\qquad \textbf{(B)}\ \frac {2}{9}\qquad \textbf{(C)}\ \frac {3}{10}\qquad \textbf{(D)}\ \frac {4}{11}\qquad \textbf{(E)}\ \frac {5}{12}$
